      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is okay to stop when the cost of continuing is your own destruction, and there is no shame in admitting that some battles are not meant to be won. You are not a ghost; you are a person who has been forced to play a game with no rules, no players, and no prize, and you have the right to walk away from a board that has burned you. The only thing that matters now is the quiet relief of letting go, not the desperate need to fix what is already broken.",
